  "market_context": "Following a large range day on NQ, conditions favored consolidation. The analyst sets up the Asia session range with the daily open/high/low marked, using the Power of 3 indicator and session boxes (Asia 20:00–02:00, London 02:00–08:30, NY 08:30–11:30).",
  "key_observation": "Both London and New York sessions failed to displace outside the Asia range. Each deviation outside the range acted like a magnet, pulling price back to equilibrium — a textbook Seek and Destroy consolidation profile.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Let the Asia session form and mark out the Asia high and low as the reference range.",
    "Step 2: Watch London attempt to sweep the Asia low — price fails to displace and trades back inside the range.",
    "Step 3: Watch London then attempt the Asia high — again no breakout/displacement, price returns inside the range.",
    "Step 4: Extend the Asia range lines as a magnet/PD array; expect price to rebalance back into the range when it deviates.",
    "Step 5: In New York, observe a move outside the range that retraces back to the equilibrium of the range.",
    "Step 6: Redraw a new premium/discount range from the NY extremes and note price gravitates back to equilibrium and the daily open.",
    "Step 7: Conclude that price is oscillating between external liquidity (range extremes) and internal liquidity (equilibrium) — a low-probability Seek and Destroy day to avoid trading."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When neither London nor New York can displace outside the Asia range, price oscillates between range extremes and equilibrium. These Seek and Destroy consolidation days are low-probability and should be avoided rather than traded.",
